Consider the following process state transition diagram. What event causes a process to move from **Running** to **Ready**?

```dot
digraph process_states {
    rankdir=LR;
    node [shape = circle];
    New -> Ready [label="admitted"];
    Ready -> Running [label="scheduler dispatch"];
    Running -> Terminated [label="exit"];
    Running -> Waiting [label="I/O or event wait"];
    Waiting -> Ready [label="I/O or event completion"];
    Running -> Ready [label="?"];
}
```
